Akhmetov’s SCM Invested 9 Billion Hryvnia to Assets Last Year

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-07-28T08:18:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/akhmetov-s-scm-invested-9-billion-hryvnia-to-assets-last-year.html
System Capital Management Group,
owned by Ukraine’s richest man, Rinat Akhmetov, invested 8.88
billion hryvnia ($1.1 billion) for development and upgrading of
its assets in 2010.  SCM’s steelmaker Metinvest BV had 4.62 billion of
investments and energy producer and distributor DTEK had 2.22
billion hryvnia, the company said in a  statement  on its web site
today. Investments in non-industrial assets of SCM accounted for
2.04 billion hryvnia.  SCM’s investment focus is modernization, new technologies,
 energy efficiency , environment protection and work safety, said
SCM Chief Executive Officer, Oleh Popov, in the statement.
Investments will “provide for long term and stable growth of
the group,” Popov said.  The Donetsk-based SCM increased investments for environment
protection and saving of resources to 2.3 billion hryvnia in
2010 from 1.6 million hryvnia a year before, the company said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
